229232bf-f81b-4238-8f48-b80e630230a3.0ebac05d-c629-4261-beca-0c02fe4c4004.prompt=Enter a value for SAusername 229232bf-f81b-4238-8f48-b80e630230a3.3d5930b8-e3c2-4b37-b370-c2349564b8be.prompt=Enter a value for SApassword 229232bf-f81b-4238-8f48-b80e630230a3.4a3804eb-e045-4f67-9f10-aef07d74d67b.prompt=Enter password 229232bf-f81b-4238-8f48-b80e630230a3.5d8645fc-3ed7-4bcf-81d5-694dabc2c827.prompt=Enter a value for disksize 229232bf-f81b-4238-8f48-b80e630230a3.837db95e-dd91-4b0d-96fd-80ee905c130a.description=
Performs a mathematical operation on two numbers or strings

Inputs\:
value1 - The first value.
value2 - The second value.
operation - The operation to perform (+ - * ^ / > < \=\= \!\= >\= <\=).

Responses\:
success -  The operation completed successfully. If a boolean operation, it evaluated to true.
failure - Something went wrong or the boolean operation returned false.

Returns\:
The raw result of the operation, for boolean values this is true or false.

Returns\:
Field 1 - The first value. Here for compatibility
Field 2 - The second value. Here for compatibility
Field 3 - The operation. Here for compatibility
formatted_result - The formatted result of the operation, for boolean values this is true or false.
229232bf-f81b-4238-8f48-b80e630230a3.868a1604-fb0a-4890-97a1-09b14a9906bf.prompt=Enter a value for custnetwork 229232bf-f81b-4238-8f48-b80e630230a3.9900a7bc-2758-4d12-aed2-68637e166de1.prompt=Enter a value for value1 229232bf-f81b-4238-8f48-b80e630230a3.a111b644-78f5-420c-b58d-73c7ac0be42f.prompt=Enter user 229232bf-f81b-4238-8f48-b80e630230a3.a38128c7-f949-4df5-9bea-0ef5a1d6f897.prompt=Enter a value for custnetwork 229232bf-f81b-4238-8f48-b80e630230a3.a6a66e82-ac7a-48a8-b236-d5f4a68eacc7.description=Create a VM from a VM template. Must specify either hostSystem, clusterName, or vmResourcePool as a target location for VMs. Input Parameters\: vmName - name of the VM that will be created with this flow templateName - name of the VM template to clone in vCenter osType - linux or windows host - vCenter host to execute against user - vCenter username password - vCenter password vmDatacenter - target Datacenter on the vCenter host for the VMs dataStore - target datastore on the vCenter host for the VMs hostSystem - target ESX host for the VMs clusterName - target cluster for the VMs vmResourcePool - target resource pool for the VMs Responses\: success - if the command completes execution and its exit code is 0 failure - otherwise Result Fields\: serviceXml - xml representation of the server created in vCenter 229232bf-f81b-4238-8f48-b80e630230a3.a7e22873-9e63-48f1-bb91-6f8a95500d7c.description=
Sleeps for "X" seconds.

Inputs\:
seconds - The number of seconds to sleep.

Responses\:
success - Slept for "X" seconds.
failure - was unable to sleep for some reason
229232bf-f81b-4238-8f48-b80e630230a3.ab3cd8ff-0e35-41ae-aada-ba4adcc5a61d.prompt=Enter a value for SAhost 229232bf-f81b-4238-8f48-b80e630230a3.description=
Provions a vCenter server

Inputs\:

host -  vCenter DNS name/IP Address
username - vCenter user
password - vCenter user password
port - vCenter port
protocol - vCenter protocol
hypervisorName - Hypervisor DNS name/IP Address
dataStore - Datastore of the hypervior
datacenterName - Datacenter name
hostname - VM Server name
templateReference -  VM Template name
osType -  OS Type of the template
CPUs - CPU Count to be assigned
Memory -  Memory Size to be assigned


Results\:

vmId - VM Identifies of the created VM
ipAddress - IP Address of the created VM
macAddress - MAC Address of the created VM
229232bf-f81b-4238-8f48-b80e630230a3.e1d7eab9-e06d-4b89-bc57-a9f92e7082df.prompt=Enter a value for SAprotocol 229232bf-f81b-4238-8f48-b80e630230a3.ea435a19-b3f1-41e6-8d39-5c8ec3fccac5.description=Check to see if the value stored in a specified flow variable, denoted by key, is null. 
Inputs\:
keyName - The key to check, i.e. the name of the flow variable.

Returns\: The value in the specified key, i.e. flow variable.

Responses\:
isNull - if the key is a null pointer, i.e. the flow variable doesn't have an assigned value.
notNull - if some value is stored in the key, i.e the flow variable has a value assigned.
229232bf-f81b-4238-8f48-b80e630230a3.f6c84071-a78b-410e-b2e0-957a71151d67.description=
Counts from one number to another number.

Inputs\:
from - The number to start counting at
to - The number to count to
incrementBy - The amount to increment by during each count.
reset - If set to true, then the counter will restart counting from the beginning.

Responses\:
has more - Not yet done counting.
failure - Something went wrong.
no more - Done counting. This will only be returned once, then counting restarts.

Returns\:
The number that was just counted.
